WorkItem.Description:
This seems to be a regression from 0.8.3. The following jsdoc comment (containing a copyright symbol) results in a compiler error (reported by VS 2012) pasted below. Once the © symbol is removed, the compiler succeeds.

This was not an issue in any previous version of TypeScript.

```
/**
    The root namespace.
    @namespace Blah
    @version 0.0.1
    @copyright Copyright © 2013 Company, Inc. All rights reserved.
*/
```

Error	3	The command ""C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft SDKs\TypeScript\tsc.exe"  --comments --module AMD --sourcemap --target ES3 "C:\TypeScriptHTMLApp1\Scripts\Core\Blah.ts" "C:\TypeScriptHTMLApp1\Scripts\Core\Blech.ts"" exited with code 1.	TypeScriptHTMLApp1
